        <!-- Academic Reflection Section -->
        <section id="reflection" class="section-content">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Academic Journey Reflection</h2>
                <div class="prose max-w-none">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">My transition into tertiary education has been a transformative journey marked by significant personal and academic growth. The shift from structured high school learning to the autonomous nature of university life required substantial adaptation.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Time Management Evolution</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Initially, I struggled with the freedom and flexibility that tertiary education offered. The absence of constant supervision meant I had to develop robust time management strategies. I implemented techniques like the Pomodoro method and digital calendaring to structure my study sessions effectively.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Adapting to Learning Styles</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">University demanded a more proactive approach to learning. I discovered that passive listening in lectures wasn't sufficient—I needed to engage actively with the material through note-taking, group discussions, and self-directed research. This shift from being taught to learning independently was challenging but ultimately rewarding.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Growth Mindset Development</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Perhaps the most valuable lesson has been embracing a growth mindset. Early setbacks in complex subjects taught me that intelligence isn't fixed but can be developed through persistence and effective strategies. I learned to view challenges as opportunities for growth rather than insurmountable obstacles.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Study Habit Refinement</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">My study habits evolved significantly. I moved from last-minute cramming to spaced repetition and interleaved practice. Creating dedicated study environments and eliminating digital distractions became crucial for maintaining focus and productivity.</p>
                    
                    <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-6">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-800 mb-2">Key Takeaways</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-green-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Self-discipline is the foundation of academic success</li>
                            <li>Effective learning requires active engagement</li>
                            <li>Resilience transforms challenges into growth opportunities</li>
                            <li>Continuous adaptation is essential in evolving educational landscapes</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Group Work Reflection Section -->
        <section id="group-work" class="section-content">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Group Work Experience Reflection</h2>
                <div class="prose max-w-none">
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">This semester's group project provided valuable insights into team dynamics and collaborative work. Using Tuckman's stages of group development as a framework, I'll reflect on our journey from formation to completion.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Forming Stage</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Our group was formed through random assignment, meaning I didn't know my group mates beforehand. The initial phase was characterized by polite formality as we cautiously explored each other's strengths and working styles. We spent our first meeting establishing basic guidelines, exchanging contact information, and discussing project expectations. There was a sense of uncertainty as we navigated this new collaborative relationship.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Storming Stage</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">As we delved deeper into the project, differences in work approaches emerged. One member preferred detailed planning while another favored rapid prototyping. This led to tension during our second week when deadlines approached and task allocation became contentious. The storming phase was challenging but necessary—it forced us to address underlying conflicts and establish clearer communication protocols.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Norming Stage</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Through open dialogue and compromise, we developed shared expectations and routines. We implemented a rotating facilitation system where each member led meetings on a weekly basis. This distributed leadership approach helped balance different working styles and ensured everyone's voice was heard. We established regular check-ins and created a shared digital workspace that became our collaborative hub.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Performing Stage</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">By the project's midpoint, we had developed into a cohesive, functioning team. Communication flowed naturally, and we could anticipate each other's needs and working patterns. The trust built during the norming stage allowed for efficient task delegation and execution. We celebrated small milestones together, which reinforced our team cohesion and motivation.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Adjourning Stage</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Our project concluded with a comprehensive debrief session where we reflected on both our final output and our collaborative process. We acknowledged the growth we'd experienced individually and as a team. While there were moments of friction throughout the semester, we parted with mutual respect and appreciation for the diverse perspectives each member brought to the project.</p>
                    
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-6">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">Lessons Learned About Teamwork</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-blue-700 space-y-1">
                            <li>Effective communication requires both speaking and active listening</li>
                            <li>Conflict, when managed constructively, can strengthen team bonds</li>
                            <li>Clear role definition prevents task duplication and gaps</li>
                            <li>Regular feedback loops are essential for continuous improvement</li>
                            <li>Diverse working styles, when leveraged properly, enhance creativity</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

